I"˘<p>When he is not exploring the origin of the elements, in a lab or in front of a computer screen, Thanassis is making science accessible to a wider audience, by participating in several science communication initiatives worldwide. This experience has enabled him to share his passion about science with the public, with a focus on children, the next generation of scientists. Below you can learn more about the initiatives he is involved in. In case you are interested in collaborating on a science communication project, feel free to <a href="mailto:psaltis.tha@duke.edu">contact</a>.</p>

